                  </hi>. I am the wife of James Perkins, and live in Hemlock-court, Carey-street. On the 15th of Sept, the prisoner came to my house—I had occasion to leave the room, and when I came back she was gone—I missed my shawl, which was safe when she came in—this is it—no one else had been in the room.</p>
